<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-11-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-11-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="812" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d812">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Eddy</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-11-13"><hi rend="italic">November 13,
                                    1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Eddy reports that an imperial proclamation was issued to-day
                            suspending the operation of the new constitution in Poland until the
                            present disorders shall cease.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>